## Additional Terms

**Clause 1 — Avoidance of Doubt (closes data-broker loophole):**

For the avoidance of doubt, "providing the software to third parties as a
hosted or managed service" in the "Limitations" section includes any use in which the
software processes telemetry data, network traffic data, or access logs
generated by or on behalf of parties other than the Licensee, regardless
of whether those third parties have direct access to the software's
interface or functionality.

**Clause 2 — Permitted Self-Defense Use (positive grant):**

Notwithstanding the foregoing, use of the software solely to monitor,
analyze, and protect infrastructure owned, operated, or exclusively
controlled by the Licensee is expressly permitted under this License.

**Clause 3 — Permitted Internal Integration:**

Use of the software as a component of an internal service or platform is
permitted, provided that the software processes only data generated by or
on behalf of the Licensee's own infrastructure. For the avoidance of
doubt, such permitted use does not extend to any deployment in which the
software processes, analyzes, or acts upon data generated by or on behalf
of the Licensee's customers, clients, or any third parties, regardless of
whether those parties have direct access to the software or awareness of
its use.